024/**
025 * Provides metadata about the API.
026 *
027 * <p>
028 * The Info Object provides metadata about the API for Swagger 2.0. The metadata can be used by the clients if needed, 
029 * and can be presented in the Swagger-UI for convenience. This includes the title, version, description, terms of service, 
030 * contact information, and license.
031 *
032 * <h5 class='section'>Swagger Specification:</h5>
033 * <p>
034 * The Info Object is composed of the following fields:
035 * <ul class='spaced-list'>
036 *    <li><c>title</c> (string, REQUIRED) - The title of the API
037 *    <li><c>version</c> (string, REQUIRED) - The version of the OpenAPI document (not the API itself)
038 *    <li><c>description</c> (string) - A short description of the API
039 *    <li><c>termsOfService</c> (string) - A URL to the Terms of Service for the API
040 *    <li><c>contact</c> ({@link Contact}) - Contact information for the exposed API
041 *    <li><c>license</c> ({@link License}) - License information for the exposed API
042 * </ul>
043 *
044 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
045 * <p class='bjava'>
046 *    <jc>// Construct using SwaggerBuilder.</jc>
047 *    Info <jv>info</jv> = <jsm>info</jsm>(<js>"Swagger Sample App"</js>, <js>"1.0.1"</js>)
048 *       .description(<js>"This is a sample server Petstore server."</js>)
049 *       .termsOfService(<js>"http://swagger.io/terms/"</js>)
050 *       .contact(
051 *          <jsm>contact</jsm>(<js>"API Support"</js>, <js>"http://www.swagger.io/support"</js>, <js>"support@swagger.io"</js>)
052 *       )
053 *       .license(
054 *          <jsm>license</jsm>(<js>"Apache 2.0"</js>, <js>"http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html"</js>)
055 *       );
056 *
057 *    <jc>// Serialize using JsonSerializer.</jc>
058 *    String <jv>json</jv> = Json.<jsm>from</jsm>(<jv>info</jv>);
059 *
060 *    <jc>// Or just use toString() which does the same as above.</jc>
061 *    <jv>json</jv> = <jv>info</jv>.toString();
062 * </p>
063 * <p class='bjson'>
064 *    <jc>// Output</jc>
065 *    {
066 *       <js>"title"</js>: <js>"Swagger Sample App"</js>,
067 *       <js>"description"</js>: <js>"This is a sample server Petstore server."</js>,
068 *       <js>"termsOfService"</js>: <js>"http://swagger.io/terms/"</js>,
069 *       <js>"contact"</js>: {
070 *          <js>"name"</js>: <js>"API Support"</js>,
071 *          <js>"url"</js>: <js>"http://www.swagger.io/support"</js>,
072 *          <js>"email"</js>: <js>"support@swagger.io"</js>
073 *       },
074 *       <js>"license"</js>: {
075 *          <js>"name"</js>: <js>"Apache 2.0"</js>,
076 *          <js>"url"</js>: <js>"http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html"</js>
077 *       },
078 *       <js>"version"</js>: <js>"1.0.1"</js>
079 *    }
080 * </p>
081 *
082 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
083 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2/#info-object">Swagger 2.0 Specification &gt; Info Object</a>
084 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/docs/specification/2-0/api-general-info/">Swagger API General Info</a>
085 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanSwagger2">juneau-bean-swagger-v2</a>
086 * </ul>
087 */
088public class Info extends SwaggerElement {
089
090   private String
091      siteName,
092      title,
093      description,
094      termsOfService,
095      version;
096   private Contact contact;
097   private License license;
098
099   /**
100    * Default constructor.
101    */
102   public Info() {}
103
104   /**
105    * Copy constructor.
106    *
107    * @param copyFrom The object to copy.
108    */
109   public Info(Info copyFrom) {
110      super(copyFrom);
111
112      this.contact = copyFrom.contact == null ? null : copyFrom.contact.copy();
113      this.description = copyFrom.description;
114      this.license = copyFrom.license == null ? null : copyFrom.license.copy();
115      this.siteName = copyFrom.siteName;
116      this.termsOfService = copyFrom.termsOfService;
117      this.title = copyFrom.title;
118      this.version = copyFrom.version;
119   }
120
121   /**
122    * Make a deep copy of this object.
123    *
124    * @return A deep copy of this object.
125    */
126   public Info copy() {
127      return new Info(this);
128   }

332   @Override /* Overridden from SwaggerElement */
333   public <T> T get(String property, Class<T> type) {
334      assertArgNotNull("property", property);
335      return switch (property) {
336         case "contact" -> toType(getContact(), type);
337         case "description" -> toType(getDescription(), type);
338         case "license" -> toType(getLicense(), type);
339         case "siteName" -> toType(getSiteName(), type);
340         case "termsOfService" -> toType(getTermsOfService(), type);
341         case "title" -> toType(getTitle(), type);
342         case "version" -> toType(getVersion(), type);
343         default -> super.get(property, type);
344      };
345   }
346
347   @Override /* Overridden from SwaggerElement */
348   public Info set(String property, Object value) {
349      assertArgNotNull("property", property);
350      return switch (property) {
351         case "contact" -> setContact(toType(value, Contact.class));
352         case "description" -> setDescription(Utils.s(value));
353         case "license" -> setLicense(toType(value, License.class));
354         case "siteName" -> setSiteName(Utils.s(value));
355         case "termsOfService" -> setTermsOfService(Utils.s(value));
356         case "title" -> setTitle(Utils.s(value));
357         case "version" -> setVersion(Utils.s(value));
358         default -> {
359            super.set(property, value);
360            yield this;
361         }
362      };
363   }
364
365   @Override /* Overridden from SwaggerElement */
366   public Set<String> keySet() {
367      var s = setBuilder(String.class)
368         .addIf(contact != null, "contact")
369         .addIf(description != null, "description")
370         .addIf(license != null, "license")
371         .addIf(siteName != null, "siteName")
372         .addIf(termsOfService != null, "termsOfService")
373         .addIf(title != null, "title")
374         .addIf(version != null, "version")
375         .build();
376      return new MultiSet<>(s, super.keySet());
377   }
